#subsaharan africa
Nilotic: tall, very dark skin
- Dinka: 5M, South Sudan
- Nuer: 2M, South Sudan, Ethiopia
- Nuba: 2M, Sudan
- Nubian: 1M, Sudan
- Luo: 5M, Great Lakes
- Maasai: 2M, Great Lakes, short hair except hunters, stretched earlobes, red blanket
- Kalenjin: 5M, Great Lakes

#sahara: islam
- Berber / Amazigh: 30M, Maghreb
- Tuareg: 3M, Sahel, nomadic herders, blue veil, matrilineal
- Fula / Fulani: 30M, Sahel, nomadic vs sedentary, dark skin

Saharan: islam, dark skin
- Toubou: 1M, nomadic herders
- Fur: 1M, Darfur
- Zaghawa / Beri: Darfur
- Masalit: Darfur

#west africa
Wolof: 5M, islam

Guinean: dark skin, colorful cloth, masks, broad nose
- Yoruba: 50M
- Igbo: 30M
- Akan: 20M, Anansi (spider), colorful Kente cloth, matrilineal
- Ewe: 10M, Voodoo
- Fon: 5M, Voodoo, female warriors

Cushitic: horn of Africa
- Oromo: 40M
- Amhara: 20M, christianity
- Somali: 20M
- Tigre + Tigrinya + Tigraya: 10M
- Afar: 3M

